15:
We aren't like the Overlords! We
need the lance to stop the purging!
18:
There's no reason for us to kill each
other—
21:
Rich words coming from Oghir's
killer.
26:
You... You and Stella took
EVERYTHING from me!
34:
This isn't over. I can summon as
many weapons as I need to—
44: The end is finally upon us...
47:
I'm sorry for lying this whole time,
Leve.
54:
We can no longer share in this
dream together...
57: Because it is time to wake.
60:
What the hell... Is that a giant eyeball
in the sky?
61: I'm not seeing things, am I?
68:
Run! Run for your lives! Don't look
back!
74: No! Let me go! Daddy! Daddyyy!
82: Our world ended a long time ago.
84:
Without a foundation, this city
floated in the Void, but its people
persisted, living in the dream of a
sleeping dragon.
86:
We performed feats of the
impossible, gaining powers inside
this realm of dreams.
88:
But what happens if you realize the
transience of this fragile existence?
97: None of this is your fault.
102:
We were supposed to be in this
together—
106:
Those with power are warping this
world, but culling their numbers was
never going to be enough... I knew
this would all end one day.
109:
I knew, but... I couldn't do it myself. I
had to wait for
someone—anyone—to set things in
motion.
112:
I'm sorry... Perhaps things would've
been different if you had used the
Dragon's power.
122:
You know, your name... Leve. It's
probably Danish.
130:
I wonder if whoever gave it to you
knew its meaning. If so, then we
have a similar wish for you.
133:
Master Mikoto... I'm coming to join
you now...
163:
You're... out of... We're about to lose
the connection!
166:
Forget the lance! You need to come
back immediately!
169:
Or else you'll never be able to come
back at all!
186:
Mr. Takamori? What are you doing
here?
190:
I thought I'd finally work toward a
dream of mine, you see.
